headline: Holiday Stock Sale: 3 Top High-Yield Dividend Stocks to Buy After the Recent Dip
summary: Stocks nosedived this week after the Federal Reserve reset its interest rate expectations for 2025.  The Federal Reserve is now forecasting only two quarter-point rate reductions next year, a more modest pace than the market had hoped.  Three stocks that are having a Fed-inspired holiday sale are Realty Income (NYSE: O), Brookfield Infrastructure (NYSE: BIPC)(NYSE: BIP), and Vici Properties (NYSE: VICI).

headline: Powell Plays Grinch
summary: Real estate equities were slammed, erasing essentially all of their late-summer gains that came ahead of the Fed's initial rate cut in September. The Equity REIT Index tumbled 4.8%.
